<h2>Patches</h2>
<p>
	This is just a mirror. Reintegrating git changes from other
	repositories back to svn is somewhat problematic. That's
	why I won't accept pull requests. Please send patches instead.
</p>
<p>
	After committing changes to your local repository you can generate
	patches using following command:
</p>
<pre>git format-patch [FIRST COMMIT]..[LAST COMMIT]</pre>
<p>
	Afterwards send them to &lt;<tt>patches<strong>@</strong>rsget.pl</tt>&gt;.
</p>

<h2>GitHub issue tracker</h2>
<p>
	If there's any problem with <strong>rsget.pl</strong> you can fill
	out an <a href="http://github.com/sparky/rsget.pl/issues">issue at
	GitHub</a>.
</p>
